commit.message:
Fix #910: Use python venv for macOS build

With this commit macOS build starts using Python virtual environment so
that our build steps can comply with PEP 668 [1].

This is only about the build procedure. There must be no behavior change
in the build artifacts.

#codehealth

 [1]: https://peps.python.org/pep-0668/

Add internal support for Gboard Personal Dictionary V1.

This CL introduces support for Gboard Personal Dictionary, which can be exported from Android Gboard.

This is only an internal support and does not include GUI support. But if users select 'auto detection' for the format, Gboard V1 will be automatically detected and imported. We can add support of the GUI format selector in the following CLs.

Change the key for NO_POS tokens.

Currently NO_POS tokens got `entry.key()` which is raw key, but it should be `reading`, a normalized version of `entry.key()`. This CL fixes the issue.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 617841535

Add space insertion mechanism for transliteration.

This CL introduces a mechanism into the EnglishVariantsRewriter, which expand variants with prefixed spaces.

While many English words are supported in Mozc, currently there is no way to insert space between words. Therefore, 'ぐーぐるじゃぱん' always becomes 'GoogleJapan',not 'Google Japan'. This is not useful, especially for new words like じぇみにぷろ→'Gemini Pro' and 'ぴくせるふぉーるど'→'Pixel Fold'. By using this mechanism, when the user select 'Pixel' for 'ぴくせる', space-prefixed candidates like ` Fold` are inserted. By selecting that candidate, users can input 'Pixel Fold' as a compound. This will be learned in subsequent inputs.

As there can be several ways to implement the same feature, I guarded this feature with a flag named "english_variation_space_insertion_mode". The current style is mode 1, and we can test mode 2 or later.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 616878136

Refactor `DateRewriter::Rewrite` by using the `Segments::Range`

This was once tried by using `Segments::iterator`, but it was abandoned because the function handling multiple segments at once made it complicated.

This patch refactors it by using `Segment::Range` instead, in preparation for supporting multiple segments in `RewriteAd`.

This patch should have no behavior changes.

This patch changes `DateRewriter` to convert "なう" to the current time.

It's the Japanese transliteration of "now", often used in modern casual conversation.
